  "notes": [
    "This pilot study investigated the prevalence and clinical implications of reversible tactile hypoesthesia in patients with myofascial trigger points.",
    "The study found that 58.7% of patients with myofascial trigger points experienced reduction in tactile hypoesthesia following trigger point injection therapy.",
    "The mechanism proposed involves inhibition of neuronal activity in the somatosensory cortex induced by nociceptive input from myofascial trigger points."
  ]
